The paper discusses techniques for recovering low-rank matrices from incomplete and indirect observations, which is a problem commonly encountered in signal processing and machine learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.IT and cs.LG are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the problem of matrix recovery and are commonly associated with low-rank matrix methods. Cs.CV is also a likely category, as it deals with image and video processing, which often involve low-rank matrix models. Cs.NA and cs.SI are less likely categories, but they could still be relevant depending on the specific applications discussed in the paper.
